You're basically taking 75% of the labs off the table.  You've got to be more flexible.

Spots likely won't be added to the labs.  Labs are limited by capacity.

Doubtful, as the class has already been expanded. If you really want to enroll this semester, I would encourage you to be more flexible. It's not known if the class will be able to be expanded in future terms. 


You may also be able to register for one lab with space, and attend another if there are enough seats in the room. You could confirm this with the faculty. This is true for the discussions, but not the labs unless there are extenuating circumstances.

As Nicole and the student said, we encourage you to be more flexible with your schedule if you want to take this class.

I'm a declared CS sophomore and the section I want is already full as is its waitlist, though I don't know how far up I am in the waitlist. I really don't want to go to 8AMs, and I heavily dislike the 11-2PMs (no lunch) and 5-8PM since I hate evening class

Is it possible that more slots will be added to each lab / discussion?
